"{\n  \"correct\": \"no\",\n  \"explanation\": \"The issue with this code is that after closing the figure with `plt.close()` on line 11, it tries to access the axis object `ax` which belongs to the closed figure on line 18. This will result in an error because the figure is already closed.\",\n  \"patch\": \"18c18\\n<ax.text(0.4, 0.4, \\\"Add a label to the current active figure\\\")\\n---\\n>ac_fig.text(0.4, 0.4, \\\"Add a label to the current active figure\\\") doesn't work here because we can't use text method directly on figure object.\\n To fix this issue, we should get the axis of the active figure before trying to add text to it. Here is the corrected patch:\\n18c18,19\\n<ax.text(0.4, 0.4, \\\"Add a label to the current active figure\\\")\\n---\\n>ac_ax = ac_fig.get_axes()[0]\\n>ac_ax.text(0.4, 0.4, \\\"Add a label to the current active figure\\\")\"\n}"